  "name": "Jeanne d'Arc",
  "title": "Maiden of Radiance",
  "secondName": "Maiden of Radiance",
  "description": "Jeanne and Mikaela d'Arc were born a strange set of twins. Mikaela arrived first, a few minutes before the last midnight of winter, while Jeanne came in the first hours of spring. The town priestess insisted the birth was an omen from His Radiance, though she never said what it foretold.\n\nThough technically the same age, it seemed only natural to call Mikaela the older sister. She was, after all, the more outgoing one, the braver one. The town cooed over her, the little warrior, so devoted to seeing Jeanne safe and happy.\n\nAnd Jeanne loved Mikaela more than anyone in the world.",
